{{Infobox person |name = Harold Robert Steacy |image = |alt = |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date|1923|6|7}} |birth_place = Ottawa, Ontario |birth_name = |death_date = {{Death date and age|2012|4|7|1923|6|7}} |death_place = Ottawa, Ontario |other_names = |known_for = |occupation = |nationality = |awards = | relations = [[Digby Denham]], grandfather }} '''Harold "Hal" Robert Steacy''' (June 7, 1923 &ndash; April 7, 2012)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://v1.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/Deaths.20120417.93291376/BDAStory/BDA/deaths|title=Harold "Hal" Robert Steacy|work=The Globe and Mail}}</ref> was a Canadian [[mineralogist]] who was the [[curator]] of the [[Canadian National Mineral Collection]] at the [[Geological Survey of Canada]] in [[Ottawa]]. The mineral [[steacyite]] is named for him.<ref>Dunn et al., 1983, p.&nbsp;473</ref>
