| authority = Lendenfeld, 1885}}

'''''Leucandra villosa''''' is a species of [[sponge]] in the taxonomic rank of the calcareous sponges (Calcarea). The sponge lives in the sea and its Sclereid consists of calcium carbonate.{{what?|date=September 2018}} 

The sponge belongs to the genus of ''[[Leucandra (sponge)|Leucandra]]'' and belongs to the family [[Grantiidae]]. The scientific name of the species was first published in 1885 by Lendenfeld.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=164401|title=WoRMS - World Register of Marine Species - Leucandra villosa Lendenfeld, 1885|website=www.marinespecies.org|language=en|access-date=2018-09-10}}</ref><ref>van Soest, R. (2011). ''Leucandra villosa'' Lendenfeld, 1885. In: Van Soest, R.W.M, Boury-Esnault, N., Hooper, J.N.A., Rützler, K, de Voogd, N.J., Alvarez de Glasby, B., Hajdu, E., Pisera, A.B., Manconi, R., Schoenberg, C., Janussen, D., Tabachnick, K.R., Klautau, M., Picton, B., Kelly, M., Vacelet, J. (2011) World Porifera database. Based on information from the [[World Register of Marine Species]] [http://www.marinespecies.org/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=164401]</ref>

